obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3524)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3524&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Reserve and Auxiliary`
  line `Air Forces Act, 1952.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) This Chapter shall come into force at once, and the remaining provisions shall come into force on`
  line `such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, and different`
  line `dates may be appointed for different provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Chapters II and III and provisions of Chapters V and VI except so far as they relate to the Auxiliary Air Force came into force`
  line `on the 15th August, 1955, vide S.R.O. 332, dated the 20th August, 1955, Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 4. Chapter IV and`
  line `provisions of Chapters V and VI relating to the Auxiliary Air Force came into force on the 15th October, 1955, vide S.R.O. 395,`
  line `dated the 15th October, 1955, Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3525)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3525&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Air Force Reserve" means any of the Air Force Reserves raised and maintained under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(b) "competent authority" means an air officer or a committee consisting of two or more air`
  line `officers appointed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) all other words and expressions used herein and defined in the Air Force Act, 1950 (15 of`
  line `1950) and not hereinbefore defined shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them by that`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3526)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. The Deputy Chief of Air Staff, vide S.R.O. 321, dated the 20th August, 1955, Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3526&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint an air officer^1`
  line `or a committee consisting of two or more air officers to perform`
  line `all or any of the functions of the competent authority under this Act for such area as may be specified in`
  line `the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3527)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Regular Air Force Reserve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3527&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may raise and maintain`
  line `in the manner hereafter in this Chapter provided an Air Force Reserve to be designated the Regular Air`
  line `Force Reserve which shall consist solely of persons transferred or appointed to it under section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3528)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Recruitment to the Regular Air Force Reserve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3528&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, by general`
  line `or special order, transfer to the Regular Air Force Reserve--`
  line
  line `(a) any officer or airman of the Air Force who under the terms and conditions of his service is`
  line `liable to serve in any Air Force Reserve if and when constituted;`
  line
  line `(b) any officer or airman of the Air Force whose commission or engagement in the Air Force has`
  line `been terminated before the commencement of this Act and who under the terms of his commission or`
  line `engagement was liable to serve in any Air Force Reserve if and when constituted;`
  line
  line `(c) any officer or airman who has served in the Air Force and has retired therefrom; and any`
  line `officer or airman so transferred shall be deemed to be a member of the said Reserve.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authority may, in such circumstances and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed, by special order, appoint to the Regular Air Force Reserve any member of the Air Defence`
  line `Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force raised and maintained under this Act, and where any such member is`
  line `so appointed, he shall cease to be a member of the Air Defence Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force, as the`
  line `case may be, and shall as from the date of such appointment be deemed to be a member of the Regular`
  line `Air Force Reserve.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority may, for reasons which in its opinion are sufficient, cancel any order`
  line `made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) and on the cancellation of such order the person in respect`
  line `of whom the order had been made shall cease to be a member of the Regular Air Force Reserve.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3529)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Classes of person in the Regular Air Force Reserve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3529&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Members of the Regular Air Force`
  line `Reserve shall be divided into the following classes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) general duties officers;`
  line
  line `(b) ground duties officers, and`
  line
  line `(c) airmen, and every officer shall be entitled on transfer or appointment to the Reserve to hold`
  line `the same rank as that which he last held in the Air Force, or the Air Defence Reserve or the Auxiliary`
  line `Air Force, as the case may be, before such transfer or appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3530)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Period of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3530&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every member of the Regular Air Force Reserve shall be liable to serve in`
  line `the Reserve--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is transferred to the Reserve under sub-section (1) of section 5, for the period of his`
  line `Reserve liability; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he is appointed to the Reserve under sub-section (2) of section 5, for the remainder of the`
  line `period for which he was liable to serve in the Air Defence Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may require any such member to serve in the Reserve for such`
  line `further period or periods not exceeding in the aggregate five years as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "period of Reserve liability" in relation to any`
  line `member of the Regular Air Force Reserve means the period for which under the terms and conditions of`
  line `his service in the Air Force he was liable to serve in any Air Force Reserve if and when constituted.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--In computing the period of Reserve liability in relation to any member of the`
  line `Regular Air Force Reserve whose commission or engagement in the Air Force was terminated before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the period which has elapsed between such termination and the date of such`
  line `commencement shall be included.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no person shall be liable to serve in the`
  line `Reserve after attaining the prescribed age.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3531)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Termination of service in the Reserve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3531&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Regular Air Force Reserve shall,`
  line `on completion of the period of his service therein, cease to be a member of the Reserve.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3532)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Constitution of Air Defence Reserve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3532&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may raise and maintain in the`
  line `manner hereafter in this Chapter provided an Air Force Reserve to be designated the Air Defence Reserve`
  line `which shall consist of persons deemed under the provisions of section 16 to be enrolled therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3533)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Classes of persons in the Air Defence Reserve.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3533&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Members of the Air Defence Reserve shall be`
  line `divided into the following classes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) general duties officers;`
  line
  line `(b) ground duties officers; and`
  line
  line `(c) airmen.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3534)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Obligation to register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3534&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every citizen of India who--`
  line
  line `(a) holds or has held a public transport pilots licence ("B" Licence) issued under the Indian`
  line `Aircraft Rules, 1937, or`
  line
  line `(b) has had not less than two hundred hours' experience of solo flying, including not less than`
  line `thirty landings, or`
  line
  line `(c) holds or has held a first class navigator's licence issued under the Indian Aircraft Rules, 1937,`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) has had at least four years aviation experience during which at least six hundred hours shall`
  line `have been spent in the air, not less than one hundred hours of such experience being experience of`
  line `navigation in the air, or`
  line
  line `(e) holds or has held a first class radio telegraph operator's licence issued under Indian Aircraft`
  line `Rules, 1937, or`
  line
  line `(f) holds or has held a radio telephone operators licence issued under Indian Aircraft Rules,`
  line `1937, or`
  line
  line `(g) holds or has held a licence as ground engineer in any of the categories A, B, C, D or X issued`
  line `under the Indian Aircraft Rules, 1937, or`
  line
  line `(h) is or was at any time employed in connection with any aerodrome or in connection with the`
  line `control and movement of aircraft, in such capacity as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `shall within the prescribed period correctly fill up, or cause to be filled up, to the best of his knowledge`
  line `and belief the prescribed form, and sign and lodge it with the competent authority nearest to his usual`
  line `place of residence or business:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply--`
  line
  line `(i) to any person belonging to any of the classes specified in clauses (a) to (f), if he has attained`
  line `the age of thirty-seven years; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to any person belonging to any of the classes specified in clauses (g) and (h), if he has attained`
  line `the age of fifty years.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the competent authority may, if it`
  line `is satisfied that the provisions of that sub-section apply to any person, by order in writing, require that`
  line `person to furnish within such time such particulars as may be specified in the order and such person shall`
  line `within the specified time furnish correctly to the best of his knowledge and belief the said particulars to`
  line `the said authority in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3535)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Liability to be called up for inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3535&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every person to whom the provisions of section 11 are`
  line `applicable shall be liable to be called up for inquiry under section 13,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he belongs to any of the classes specified in clauses (a) to (f) of sub-section (1) of section 11,`
  line `until he has completed his thirty-seventh year, and`
  line
  line `(b) if he belongs to any of the classes specified in clauses (g) and (h) of the said sub-section, until he`
  line `has completed his fiftieth year.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3536)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Calling-up for inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3536&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority may cause to be served on any person for the`
  line `time being liable to be called up for inquiry under section 12 a written notice stating that he is called up`
  line `for inquiry regarding his fitness for service in the Air Defence Reserve and requiring him to present himself to such person and at such place and at such time as may be specified in the notice and to submit`
  line `himself to inquiry by the said person`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3537)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Medical examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3537&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every person called up for inquiry under section 13 shall, if and when`
  line `required by the competent authority, present himself for examination before such medical officer as may`
  line `be directed by that authority and, for the purposes of such examination, shall comply with the directions`
  line `of the medical officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3538)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Registration of persons considered fit for enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3538&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If, after such inquiry and medical`
  line `examination as aforesaid, the competent authority considers a person fit for enrolment in the Air Defence`
  line `Reserve, it shall inform him accordingly and enter his name and other prescribed particulars in a register`
  line `maintained in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3539)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Calling up for service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3539&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority may cause to be served on any person whose`
  line `name is entered in the register maintained in pursuance of section 15 a written notice stating that he is`
  line `called up for service in the Air Defence Reserve and requiring him to present himself at such place and`
  line `time and to such authority as may be specified in the notice; and the person upon whom the notice is`
  line `served shall be deemed to be enrolled in the Reserve as from the day so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3540)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Period of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3540&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person deemed to be enrolled in the Air Defence Reserve shall be`
  line `liable for service--`
  line
  line `(a) if he belongs to any of the classes specified in clauses (a) to (f) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 11, until he has completed his forty-second year;`
  line
  line `(b) if he belongs to any of the classes specified in clauses (g) and (h) of the said sub-section, until`
  line `he has completed his fifty-fifth year.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such person, on attaining the age specified in sub-section (1), shall cease to be a member of`
  line `the Air Defence Reserve.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3541)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Constitution of Auxiliary Air Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3541&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may raise and maintain in`
  line `the manner hereafter in this Chapter provided an Air Force to be designated the Auxiliary Air Force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may constitute such number of squadrons and units of the Auxiliary Air`
  line `Force as it thinks fit and may disband or reconstitute any squadron or unit.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3542)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Classes of persons in the Auxiliary Air Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3542&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Members of the Auxiliary Air Force shall be`
  line `divided into the following classes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) general duties officers;`
  line
  line `(b) ground duties officers; and`
  line
  line `(c) airmen.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3543)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Officers of the Auxiliary Air Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3543&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The President may grant to such person as he thinks fit a`
  line `commission as an officer in the Auxiliary Air Force with designation of rank corresponding to that of any`
  line `commissioned officer in the Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3544)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Persons eligible for enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3544&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any citizen of India may offer himself for enrolment in the`
  line `Auxiliary Air Force and may, if he satisfies the prescribed conditions, be so enrolled on such terms as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3545)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Period of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3545&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every officer and every enrolled person shall, subject to any rules that may`
  line `be made in this behalf under this Act, be required to serve in the Auxiliary Air Force for a period of five`
  line `years from the date of his appointment or enrolment but may, after the completion of his period of`
  line `service, volunteer to serve therein for further periods each of not more than five years' duration.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3546)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Termination of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3546&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The service of any officer or enrolled person in the Auxiliary Air`
  line `Force may, at any time before the completion of his period of service, be terminated by such authority and`
  line `under such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3547)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3547&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, constitute--`
  line
  line `(a) for the whole of India, a Central Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) for each State, a State Advisory Committee; and`
  line
  line `(c) for every unit of the Auxiliary Air Force, a Unit Advisory Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Central Advisory Committee to advise the Central Government on`
  line `matters connected with the Auxiliary Air Force generally, of the State Advisory Committee to advise the`
  line `Central Government on matters connected with the formation of squadrons or units in the State and`
  line `squadrons or units already stationed in the State.`
  line
  line `(3) The duties, powers and procedure of Advisory Committees and in particular the matters in respect`
  line `of which the Advisory Committees may be called upon to give advice shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3548)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Liability to be called up for service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3548&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Every member of an Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary`
  line `Air Force shall, during the period of his service, be liable to be called up--`
  line
  line `(a) for training for such period as may be prescribed and for medical examination,`
  line
  line `(b) for service in aid of the civil power,`
  line
  line `(c) for Air Force service in India or abroad.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3549)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Application of Air Force Act, 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3549&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every member of an Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary`
  line `Air Force shall, when called up for training, medical examination or for service under this Act, be subject`
  line `to the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), and the rules made thereunder in the same manner as a person`
  line `belonging to the Air Force and holding the same rank is subject to the said Act and rules and shall`
  line `continue to be so subject until duly released from such training, medical examination or service, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (3550)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Reinstatement in civil employ of persons required to perform service under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3550&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) It`
  line `shall be the duty of every employer by whom a person called up under section 25 is employed to grant`
  line `him such leave as may be necessary and to reinstate him in his employment on the termination of the`
  line `period during which he has been so called up in an occupation and under conditions not less favourable to`
  line `him than those which would have been applicable to him had he not been so called up:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the employer refuses to reinstate such person or denies his liability to reinstate such`
  line `person, or if for any reason the reinstatement of such person is represented by the employer to be`
  line `impracticable, either party may refer the matter to the prescribed authority and that authority shall, after`
  line `considering all matters which may be put before him and after making such further inquiry into the matter`
  line `as may be prescribed, pass an order--`
  line
  line `(a) exempting the employer from the provisions of this section, or`
  line
  line `(b) requiring him to re-employ such person on such terms as that authority thinks suitable, or`
  line
  line `(c) requiring him to pay to such person by way of compensation for failure or inability to`
  line `re-employ a sum not exceeding an amount equal to six months' remuneration at the rate at which his`
  line `last remuneration was payable to him by the employer.`
  line
  line `(2) If any employer fails to obey the order of any such authority as is referred to in the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, and the court`
  line `by which an employer is convicted under this section shall order him (if he has not already been so`
  line `required by the said authority) to pay to the person whom he has failed to re-employ a sum equal to six`
  line `months remuneration at the rate at which his last remuneration was payable to him by the employer, and`
  line `any amount so required to be paid either by the said authority or by the court shall be recoverable as if it`
  line `were a fine imposed by such court.`
  line
  line `(3) In any proceeding under this section it shall be a defence for an employer to prove that the person`
  line `formerly employed did not apply to the employer for reinstatement within a period of two months from`
  line `the termination of the period during which he was called up under section 25.`
  line
  line `(4) The duty imposed by sub-section (1) upon an employer to grant leave to a person such as is`
  line `described in that sub-section or to reinstate him in his employment shall attach to an employer who,`
  line `before such person is actually called up under section 25, terminates his employment in circumstances`
  line `such as to indicate an intention to evade the duty imposed by that sub-section and such intention shall be`
  line `presumed until the contrary is proved if the termination takes place after the issue of an order relating to`
  line `that person under section 25.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (3551)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Preservation of certain rights of persons called up for service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3551&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `When any person called up`
  line `under section 25 has any rights under any provident fund or superannuation fund or other scheme for the`
  line `benefit of employees maintained in connection with the employment he relinquishes, he shall continue,`
  line `during the period for which he has been so called up and if he is reinstated, until such reinstatement under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, to have in respect of such fund or scheme such rights as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (3552)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Pay and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3552&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every member of an Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force`
  line `shall, during the period of training or active service, receive such pay and allowances as are admissible to`
  line `an officer or airman, as the case may be, in the corresponding rank, branch or trade of the Air Force.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such member was in any employment immediately before he is called up for training`
  line `under section 25, the employer shall, during the period of the training, be liable to pay to him the`
  line `difference, if any, between the pay and allowances which he would have received from the employer if he`
  line `had not been called up for such training and the pay and allowances which he receives as such member`
  line `while under training.`
  line
  line `(3) If any employer refuses or fails to pay to any such member the difference in pay and allowances`
  line `as provided in sub-section (2), such difference in pay and allowances may, on application by the member`
  line `to the prescribed authority, be recovered from the employer in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (3553)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3553&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person refuses or without lawful excuse (the burden of proving which shall`
  line `lie upon such person) neglects to comply fully with the requirements of sub-section (1) of section 11 or of`
  line `any order made under sub-section (2) of that section or with the requirements of section 14, he shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person wilfully fails to comply with any notice issued under section 13 or section 16, he`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (3554)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Service of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3554&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any notice or order to be served on any person for the purposes of this Act`
  line `may be sent by post to that person at his last known address or may be served upon him in such other`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (3555)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Competent authority to be public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3555&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act every competent`
  line `authority and where the competent authority consists of a committee of two or more air officers, every`
  line `member of the committee shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (3556)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of Central Government to grant exemptions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3556&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, for`
  line `special reasons and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, by order exempt any person from any`
  line `obligation or liability under this Act or any particular provision thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (3557)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3557&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the composition and strength of any Air Force Reserve;`
  line
  line `(b) the circumstances in which and the conditions subject to which any officer or airman may be`
  line `transferred or appointed to the Regular Air Force Reserve under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the age beyond which persons shall not be liable to serve in the Regular Air Force Reserve;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and manner in which the particulars required by sub-section (2) of section 11 shall be`
  line furnished;
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which registers shall be maintained in pursuance of section 15, the`
  line `particulars to be entered therein, and the correction or revision of such particulars from time to time;`
  line
  line `(f) the pay or allowances payable to persons called up for inquiry or medical examination under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) the terms and conditions subject to which a person may be enrolled as a member of the`
  line `Auxiliary Air Force;`
  line
  line `(h) the authority by which and the conditions subject to which the service of any officer or`
  line `enrolled person in the Auxiliary Air Force may be terminated;`
  line
  line `(i) the constitution and the duties, powers and procedure of Advisory Committees to be`
  line `constituted under section 24;`
  line
  line `(j) the period and manner of training of members of any Air Force Reserve and the Auxiliary Air`
  line Force;
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which the rank of any member of an Air`
  line `Force Reserve may be determined;`
  line
  line `(l) the constitution of the authority for the purpose of section 27 and the manner in which such`
  line `authority may conduct any inquiry under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) the authority to which an application under sub-section (3) of section 29 may be made and the`
  line `manner in which the difference in the pay and allowances may be recovered under that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner in which any notice or order issued or made under this Act may be served;`
  line
  line `(o) the conditions subject to which any person may be exempted from any obligation or liability`
  line `under this Act or any particular provision thereof;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which under this Act is to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under this section may provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (3558)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3558&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of sections 2, 4 and 31, Act 45 of 1950.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act,`
  line `1957 (36 of 1957), s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (3559)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `. Repealed.`
  content `[Repeal of Act 36 of 1939.] Rep. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498&sectionId=3559&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00021_195262_1517807328498
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
